{
  "stem": "10353.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And then we were marched into a barrack.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And we were given a wooden bunk, bunk bed, three tiers.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And that I remember, it sort of sunk in for the first time that what-- what really took place, what happened.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] It was like coming out from a dream and I remember breaking out in tears.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "[DRINKS] Being away such huge distance from your home town, not knowing what happened to your parents, what happened to your sisters.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "And here you are just nothing.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The following day, we were told to line up and to go to the showers, to leave the clothes on one side and you come out on the other side.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The rumor was that we are going to get some special clothes on the other side.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "We took the shower, no soap or anything of the sort.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I remember by the time we came out on the other side, we were told no, no, to go back and to take back our own clothes.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] So we took back our own clothes and we went back to the barracks again.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] All of a sudden, an order came that everybody should go back to the tent and to pick up their things that they have surrendered.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "We didn't know what happened, so we went back, we picked up whatever there was, and we were marched back to our barracks.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "So the rumor was that we will be left with our own civilian clothes and the idea was apparently-- now, these were all rumors-- that we are going to be kept for eventual trade for some trucks or coffee and that type of thing.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Nothing was confirmed or officially announced.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were left with our own clothes and, well, that was it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we were put into those barracks.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And from then on, so every morning we would get something that looked like coffee.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And around noon time, we would get a turnip soup, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a thick turnip soup.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And at night, again, we would get a little bit of that ersatz cafe, you know, coffee substitution.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "From time-- Were you with any friends?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Were you're with people that you knew?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "You made friends.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You made friends, although I did have some people-- as a matter of fact, I got to know some people in the orphanage that we came together in the-- from the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the whole group, that 4,500 people or so, were billeted in several barracks.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they consisted primarily of highly intellectual people, mostly from Budapest, and doctors, lawyers, professors, writers, actors, you name it.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were-- we managed to sort of survive on-- every night somebody would give us a little pep talk of some sort.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But we were hermetically enclosed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know what was going on in the outside world at all.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We didn't know what happened to anybody.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were in there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we couldn't-- from time to time, they would take us out to work, either to clean the gutters or to go out in the woods to chop wood for the kitchen.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- But most of the day you just stayed in the barracks?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we sort of worked around the camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We cleaned up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We we weren't-- we weren't in charge of any real heavy physical work.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But every morning, the women who were on the other side of the camp, they were mostly in the red barracks, they were marched-- there was a weaving factory adjacent to our camp, which was adjacent to the crematoria.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They would be marching through on the main road of the camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And all of a sudden, somebody yelled-- somebody came and told me that the women would be marched by SS women, surrounded or guarded by SS women with dogs and-- but they would be yelling out names, you know.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Wherever you went and you saw a group of people, you would be yelling out names.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe you would find somebody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the boys in my barrack came and told me-- because they would be standing at the gates, you know, that was wired, electrically wired-- that they heard that one girl called my name.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the following day I went out and I yelled out, who called my name?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was mostly Hungarian women-- not mostly, but all of them were Hungarian women.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Columns upon columns were going to work.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And sure enough, it was a girl that I knew from my home town, was my girlfriend.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we made a connection and we started to trade a little bit.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
